The basics of gemmology are introduced. Identification of different stones and use of necessary instruments. Magnifying glass and its use. An overview of stone cutting types, quality assessment and maintenance.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide general knowledge of stones and minerals, their characteristics and determination methods.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the subject, the student: - have familiarized themselves with the properties of various stones and minerals; - knows how to use suitable tools for determining stones; - knows how and with which tools to determine stones; - has an overview of the cut types of gemstones; - knows how to evaluate the quality of stones and how to choose them for professional work; - knows how to care for different gemstones.
